# .gitignore — platform-dev-blueprint
#
# Deliberately minimal. This is a steering/documentation workspace, not a build
# project — there is no compiled output to ignore. Keep chat-context/ tracked:
# WORKLIST, STARTER, sprints/, and findings/ are the living state and travel
# with the repo. Do NOT add chat-context/ here.

# --- OS / editor noise ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*~
.idea/
.vscode/

# --- QS runtime output ---
# The QS tool prints its report to the session; any on-disk status dump it may
# write is generated state, not source. Adjust these patterns when the QS tool
# in scripts/ is finalized.
qs-last.*
*.qs-out
scripts/**/__pycache__/

# --- Local secrets / env (instance-side, never in the blueprint) ---
# PROJECT.md is secret-free by design (paths + slugs only). These guard against
# an instance dropping local credentials into the workspace.
.env
.env.*
*.local
secrets.*

# --- Keep empty tracked dirs ---
# .gitkeep files are intentional — never ignore them.
!.gitkeep
